        "committer": {
          "name": "Wang Shilong",
          "email": "wshilong@ddn.com",
          "date": "2014-10-30 06:16:47.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-5568 lnet: fix memory leaks and avoid double free",
        "message": "LU-5568 lnet: fix memory leaks and avoid double free\n\nProblem is caused by following commit:\n8fab48a8ef0bad6961c2ca1e2959726252ba43ac\n\nlnet_startup_lndni() should free @ni since caller dosen't\ndo it, and if we have added this network into global list,\nlnet_shutdown_lndni() will free @ni memory in that error path,\nso we need not call lnet_ni_free() explictly, otherwise double\nfree happens.\n\nSigned-off-by: Wang Shilong <wshilong@ddn.com>\nChange-Id: I41bb8e5a5ddf521aa67fd877a183031851b5ff07\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
